Intestinal fibrosis in **Crohn’s disease (CD)**—a **complication in 50% of patients**—is driven by **epithelial-to-mesenchymal transition (EMT)** within **ulcerated mucosa**, where **TGF-β/BMP signal integration**, **YAP/TAZ mechanosensing**, and **myofibroblast contractility** converge to form **dense, non-reversible strictures**.

